%20to%20cause%20damage%20to%20crops%2C%20leading%20to%20agricultural%20losses%2C%20and%20they%20have%20the%20unusual%20ability%20to%20infest%20electrical%20equipment%2C%20including%20cars%20and%20computers.%20This%20unique%20behaviour%20can%20result%20in%20technical%20malfunctions%20and%20costly%20repairs%2C%20making%20the%20presence%20of%20red%20fire%20ants%20a%20multifaceted%20problem%20wherever%20they%20establish%20themselves%20as%20invasive%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20article%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0960982223009740%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECurrent%20Biology%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20September%2011%2C%20a%20group%20of%20ant%20experts%20confirmed%20that%20the%20species%20has%20made%20its%20way%20to%20Sicily-the%20ant's%20first%20official%20sighting%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BS.%20invicta%20is%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20invasive%20species.%20It%20can%20spread%20alarmingly%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20lead%20author%20Mattia%20Menchetti%20of%20the%20Institute%20of%20Evolutionary%20Biology%20in%20Spain.%20%26quot%3BFinding%20this%20species%20in%20Italy%20was%20a%20big%20surprise%2C%20but%20we%20knew%20this%20day%20would%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20originated%20in%20South%20America%2C%20S.%20invicta%20has%20spread%20quickly%2C%20flying%20into%20wind%20streams%20to%20travel%20farther%20on%20the%20local%20level.%20But%20humans%20have%20also%20helped%20it%20spread%20both%20through%20the%20maritime%20trade%20industry%20and%20by%20shipping%20plant%20products%2C%20enabling%20it%20to%20establish%20itself%20in%20Australia%2C%20China%2C%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20throughout%20the%20United%20States%20in%20less%20than%20a%20century.%20Europe%20has%20evaded%20them%20for%20longer%20than%20expected%2C%20say%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20vast%20number%20of%20alien%20ant%20species%20cu